        %p.zeta My body of work includes consumer-facing websites, content management systems, emails and rich media advertising.
        -# %p.zeta Below is a selection of recently completed projects. Click the buttons to read the accompanying case study for each piece.
        %p.zeta Below is a selection of recently completed projects. Full case studies coming soon.
    %article.featured
      .column-one
        = image_tag "pages/home/work_better.jpg", alt: "Better"
      .column-two
        %header
          %h1.gamma.bold-weight.accent{ "data-mobile-font-size" => "epsilon" } Better
          = link_to content_tag(:span, "better.org.uk"), "http://www.better.org.uk", class: "external-link", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener noreferrer"
        %p{ "data-mobile-font-size" => "zeta" } I've worked with GLL on various projects over the last 4 years. The previous iteration of their Better Leisure website was the first project I cut my teeth on as a Junior at a digital agency.
        %p{ "data-mobile-font-size" => "zeta" } This was a major re-design of the previous site, freshening it up with responsive templates, adding new sections and keeping the core functionality of the previous build.
        %p{ "data-mobile-font-size" => "zeta" } I completed the vast majority of the front-end development of the site, including the styling, all of the vanilla JavaScript functionality, some React work and i18n internationalisation.
        %p.bold-weight Full case study coming soon.
        -# = link_to content_tag(:span, "Read on"), "/work/better", class: "button button-primary"

    .group
      %article.regular
        .column-one
          = image_tag "pages/home/work_london_sport.jpg", alt: "London Sport Funding Search Tool"
        .column-two
          %header
            %h1.zeta.bold-weight.accent{ "data-mobile-font-size" => "epsilon" } London Sport Funding Search Tool
            = link_to "funding.londonsport.org", "http://funding.londonsport.org", class: "eta external-link", target: "_blank"
          %p.eta{ "data-mobile-font-size" => "zeta" } London Sport approached us with the brief of turning their internally circulated list of grant-funded projects into a fully-responsive, interactive search tool. As the sole front-end on the project, I worked closely with the back-end team and the client to deliver their requirements.
          %p.eta.bold-weight{ "data-mobile-font-size" => "eta" } Full case study coming soon.
          -# = link_to content_tag(:span, "Read on"), "/work/london-sport-funding-search-tool", class: "button button-primary"
      %article.regular
        .column-one
          = image_tag "pages/home/work_portland_resourcing.jpg", alt: "Portland Resourcing"
        .column-two
          %header
            %h1.zeta.bold-weight.accent{ "data-mobile-font-size" => "epsilon" } Portland Resourcing
            = link_to "portlandresourcing.com", "http://www.portlandresourcing.com", class: "eta external-link", target: "_blank"
          %p.eta{ "data-mobile-font-size" => "zeta" } Portland Resourcing approached the development team to take over the maintenance of their existing site. They wanted to keep the look and feel, whilst improving performance. We did this by stripping away layers of bloat from things like unnecessary jQuery, poorly written views and mismanaged stylesheets.
          %p.eta.bold-weight{ "data-mobile-font-size" => "eta" } Full case study coming soon.
          -# = link_to content_tag(:span, "Read on"), "/work/portland-resourcing", class: "button button-primary"
